Kenya’s Dickson Chumba cruised to victory in the 2018 Tokyo Marathon cutting the tape in a time of 2:05.30 to win the men’s race in the Japanese capital. It was his second win in the marathon after his exploits in 2014 and finishing third in the last three editions. Yuta Shitara prevented a Kenyan 1-2 as he came in second ahead of Amos Kipruto and Gideon Kipketer who timed 2:06:33 and 2:06:47. The women’s race was won by Ethiopia’s Birhane Dibaba who timed 2:19:51 with Helah Kiprop the best Kenyan finisher in fifth place. Last year’s winner and favourite Wilson Kipsang did not finish the race. More to follow…  